to 43 - close to 44 now..and im getting tired of quadding, i really am..<br>
I don't beg for crack anymore - and i busted my ass getting jboots (got them at 35 w/ a lvl 40) few deaths and some mad tactics for when the sk's fear broke - but we each got a ring..<br>
So now i can solo - whoopdey dee..its soo boring and not that fun. I moved over to terris thule because a rl friend suggested it - and knew a great mid lvl guild we could get into. So i abandoned my lvl 18 rogue and made a wiz - because he said it would be better for grouping pourposes.<br>
I got groups in the 20s in loio - but i was green - what non twink isnt?? Well...learned how to play my character there..did a bind loop death at the ghost camp in unrest at 30 - put me back to 18 (my guild Incarnate all dropped what they were doing to camp all potential aggro untill a GM could kick me out thank god - i didnt come back 5)...redid 18-30 solo for the most part -guild groups (no more bad fort groups in loio) Then i got to 30 - tried OT - poo, hard to get a group, made it to 35 got my boots (u know how bad it sucks kiting without??) Figured screw working on groups ill just solo - figured it would get better when i get to the 40s<br>
I havent got 1 group in sol b yet (1 offer..and the tank asked me to clarity his cleric) and 1 group in DL<br>
...i was so happy to get the DL group that i stayed on untill i was falling asleep - played for 4-6 hours w/ them.<br>
Played the best i could (i was getting aggro when i would buff myself...who knows) and jesus the mobs were dropping would take a lil while for the tank to get it to 2/3s then boom...next pull. Never once was my mana lower than the clerics - no waiting on me ot med, no holding the group up - and i was keeping up w/ every1 for the most part and doing my fair share<br>
But now aside from the occasional raid - i cant ever get a group...unless i bust my ass for 1<br>
<br>
Now for the real rant..<br>
<br>
It amazes me how many of you dipshits got into your 40s...ill be roaming looking for a group or just going to trans some1 and see a wiz nuke asap on the pull and run around randomly trying to get the tanks to taunt off of you. I like my wiz...and i know that there's some balancing issues that need to be done to make us typically more desireable in low lvl groups (you cant really twink a wizard...no such thing as a high lvl mob dropped spell thats useable at the 20s) but so called wizard's ...or people with enough dumb luck who can ride on other people's work are ruining the possibility of getting a group for us.<br>
<br>
So please....wait till the tank has fucking aggro<br>
Who gives a shit if ur fm...or if u never go below 80 - thats good, you can save lives w/ that (ie healers oom - mob's low life but wont turn to flee because a tank's about to drop..)<br>
<br>
Oh and...all you jackasses - when u do get aggro, and you will...let it beat thru steelskin...then take a step back... mob doesnt turn...let it beat u some more - and take a step back<br>
thats ONE ....i repeat ONE step - dont make the rogue miss their backstab, or a tank miss their taunt...it gets annoying, and makes wizards not wanted<br>
<br>
One day i looked at a rogues damage table/logs somewhere - wizzie can nuke harder, but why do groups prefer rogues? Because they're melee - they hit evade and turn auto attack off yet stay put. and dont give me that mana regen shit - because its not a problem if u dont get aggro<br>
